race.comment: MAID OF MOOLAH (6) has come back a much stronger mare this time in and finally drawn a decent gate. Won her last two starts at the provincials with plenty up the sleeve. Produced a solid set of figures when leading throughout from the wide draw over 1300m at Hawkesbury. Braith Nock retains the ride, and she can upset some of her more fancied rivals. LIGHTNING GLORY (10) showed blistering speed from the outset when leading throughout for an effortless victory over 1250m at Newcastle. Will give them something to catch again from the better draw. Looks up to this. EXTREME DIAMOND (7) shouldered the 61kg second up when a fast finishing second over 1100m at Goulburn. Will benefit with the claim and must be respected. The race doesn't end there. EQUERRY (12) improving colt who comes here in peak condition. Started fav when a fighting winner over 1400m at Kembla Grange in maiden grade. Maps well and Rawiller goes on.
